This paper is primarily focused on person re-identification, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel network architecture that uses adversarial learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep representations for person re-ID, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of real-world scenarios, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) or cryptography and security (cs.CR).
